<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,760,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1426,1453]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">Comments.</emphasis>
This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName authority="alternata" authorityName="alternata (Say" authorityYear="1825" box="[636,880,1427,1453]" class="Asteroidea" family="Luidiidae" genus="Luidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Paxillosida" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="alternata" subSpecies="alternata">
<emphasis box="[636,880,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">L. alternata alternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Trindade. One specimen was observed and photographed 
<emphasis box="[313,383,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">in situ</emphasis>
in Trindade (Ponta da Calheta, 
<date box="[746,877,1463,1489]" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" value="2018-07-31">31.vii.2018</date>
, at a depth of about 
<quantity box="[1110,1171,1462,1490]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
), but escaped after collection. However, its distinctive color pattern, number of arms, and more importantly, the presence of a prominent spine in the center of some paxillae of the abactinal region lead us to identify the Trindade specimen as 
<taxonomicName authority="alternata" authorityName="alternata (Say" authorityYear="1825" class="Asteroidea" family="Luidiidae" genus="Luidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Paxillosida" pageId="16" pageNumber="47" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="alternata" subSpecies="alternata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="47">L. alternata alternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
